      • moveTo

        void moveTo​(int x,
            int y)
        Move cell to the specified location. In contrast with setX(int)/setY(int) methods, this method will re-position complete cell structure: this cell together with all child cells. For EditorCell_Collection this method can trigger re-layout process for some child cells by calling requestRelayout() method on corresponding cells.

        For example, if wrapping (indent) layout is attached to this EditorCell_Collection, then layout logic uses X coordinate of first (or parent) cell to determine cell wrapping position. As a result of moveTo(int, int) request, complete re-layout for cell subtree should be triggered to determine new wrapping position.

        In case of EditorCell_Collection this method will delegate all layout-specific cell processing to the corresponding CellLayout

        Parameters:
        x - new X-coordinate
        y - new Y-coordinate

      • findLeaf

        EditorCell findLeaf​(int x,
                    int y)
        Searching for a cell (child cell if this is EditorCell_Collection) at the specified position. Returns the leaf (non-collection) cell or null if corresponding cell was not found.

        EditorCell_Collection implementors can perform a translation of x,y coordinates in this method.

        Parameters:
        x - -coordinate
        y - -coordinate
        Returns:
        cell at the specified position

      • findNearestLeafOnLine

        EditorCell findNearestLeafOnLine​(int x,
                                 int y,
                                 org.jetbrains.mps.util.Condition<EditorCell> condition)
        Searching for the cell within the editor "line" which is closest to the specified position by x-coordinate. First searching for the cells on the specified "line" (intersecting with specified y-coordinate) and then looking for the best match (the closest cell). Returns the leaf (non-collection) cell or null if corresponding cell was not found.

        EditorCell_Collection implementors can perform a translation of x,y coordinates in this method.

        Parameters:
        x -
        y -
        condition -
        Returns:

        List<SimpleEditorMessage> getMessages()
